19/01/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Paddy Ashdown has appointed US diplomat Susan Johnson as Brcko District Supervisor and Deputy High Representative, according to a statement issued Sunday (18 January). It cited Johnson's previous experience with governments in transition, including embassy duties in Romania, Russia and Pakistan.
Also Sunday, a bomb reportedly planted in his vehicle killed Taib Torlakovic, a wartime military police commander and alleged organised crime boss in BiH. Police are investigating the blast. (OHR Sources - 19/01/04; PBS BiH, Pincom.info, Onasa, BBC, RTRS - 18/01/04)
